                  "pageId": 1599008,
                  "revisionId": 2719619,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "With this augment, two daggers will seek out enemies every second and remain embedded for three seconds before returning to orbit Kullervo, with any orbiting daggers indicated on the UI. The ability otherwise behaves as normal (dealing self-damage if any daggers are still orbiting Kullervo when the ability ends, targeted enemies receiving a maximum of three daggers, and so on)."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Volatile Recompense",
                  "pageId": 1599008,
                  "revisionId": 2719619,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Struck enemies will not be targeted by following volleys until the daggers embedded in them expire. If no valid targets are in range, daggers will stop spawning until a valid target is in range."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Volatile Recompense",
                  "pageId": 1599008,
                  "revisionId": 2719619,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The daggers generate Overguard every 0.6s as long as sufficient targets are in range."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Volatile Recompense",
                  "pageId": 1599008,
                  "revisionId": 2719619,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "If Kullervo's Overguard is depleted less than 0.1s after a dagger generates it, there will be an opening where attacks can damage his health before the next dagger can restore the gate."
